FBIS4-63477 "drsov099_f_94016" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 National Affairs Civil Congress Supports Crimea's Sovereignty Civil Congress Supports Crimea's Sovereignty LD2005163594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1410 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005163594 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Text] Odessa, 20 May -- "The aggressive aspirations of the imperial-military Kiev, which is striving to trample down Crimea's sovereignty, deserve resolute condemnation. Yuriy Meshkov will not be right if he yields to blackmail and agrees to compromises," this is how Lev Vershynin, the cochairman of the Civil Congress of Ukraine, commented on the latest developments in Crimea in an interview with a UNIAR correspondent. He said that the Odessa branch of the Civil Congress will issue a relevant statement in connection with the latest events in Crimea.
